Home Affairs Minister Aaron Motsoaledi speaks to #eNCA on this sensitive issue. #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - South African officials are working hard to deal with the influx of foreign nationals, according to Home Affairs Minister Aaron Motsoaledi. The brutal murder of a Zimbabwean man in Diepsloot has brought xenophobia back into focus. There's also outrage at police allegedly identifying foreign nationals by asking people to name parts of the body in South African languages. Watch the video above for more details.